an period, A Proximate Remove explores this question by mapping the destabilizing aesthetic, affective, and phenomenological dimensions of experiencing intimacy and loss. The spatiotemporal fissures Reginald Jackson calls ";proximate removes"; suspend belief in prevailing structures. Beyond issues of sexuality, A Proximate Remove contends that Genji queers in its reluctance to romanticize or reproduce a flawed social order. This hesitation enhances how we engage premodern texts and question contemporary disciplinary stances.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Japanese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520382558zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520382558zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520382558/original  a978-3-11-073915-2 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075412-4 EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb